,{"name":"Isabelle","meanings":["form of   Isabel  , now in frequent use in the English-speaking world."]},{"name":"Isobella","meanings":["form of   Isabel  , which has been popular in England since the 18th century and has recently become the preferred form of the name."]},{"name":"Isobelle","meanings":["Originally a Spanish version of   Elizabeth  , which was coined by deletion of the first syllable and alteration of the final consonant sound to one that can normally end a word in Spanish. The name was imported into France in the early Middle Ages, and thence into England. It was a royal name, and its enduring popularity may have been enhanced by the fact that it was borne by a queen of England—  Isabella  (  1296–1358 ), daughter of  Philip IV  of France—even though she led a turbulent life and eventually had her husband,  Edward II , murdered."]},{"name":"Isobel","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Isabel ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":16,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Isabel was born about 1274, in Oxton, Cheshire, England. She had at least 1 son with Roger Domville. She died in 1310, at the age of 37."},"et":{"about 1274–1310":"umbes 1274–1310","1239–1289":"1239–1289","1280–1365":"1280–1365","1274–1310":"1274–1310","1239":"1239","about 1280":"umbes 1280","1289":"1289","1310":"1310","1365":"1365","1274":"1274","1280":"1280","about 1274":"umbes 1274","1290":"1290","Oxton, Cheshire, England":"Oxton, Cheshire, England","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1274–1310":"noin 1274–1310","1239–1289":"1239–1289","1280–1365":"1280–1365","1274–1310":"1274–1310","1239":"1239","about 1280":"noin 1280","1289":"1289","1310":"1310","1365":"1365","1274":"1274","1280":"1280","about 1274":"noin 1274","1290":"1290","Oxton, Cheshire, England":"Oxton, Cheshire, England","C